AB  - We investigate the effects of the first voluntary shift of a NYSE firm (Aeroflex) to Nasdaq. The switch announcement has resulted in a significant positive abnormal return, in subsequent narrowing of the daily bid–ask spread, and in significant increase of the daily volume. We fail to find evidence that the switch is responsible for making Aeroflex’ stock behave more like a “Nasdaq stock”.
